				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Haste worth the cash?<a name="57451"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 19 04 3:43 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>depending on your local bazaar market you can most likely make 10000-20000 tributepoints out of those 2k cash. 
<br />

<br />
(look for items that give a ratio of 5 points per 1 pp or better - on my server I quite easily find items for 6:1 and meanwhile only take items with a ratio of 8:1 or better, because I already got quite a lot points)
<br />

<br />
Now let's assume you only get 10k tributepoints for your 2k pp.
<br />

<br />
At lvl 30 you have access to the Tier2 of the tributebuff &quot;Swift Arms&quot;, which is - if memory doesn't cheat me - 26% haste for 12 points/10 minutes.
<br />

<br />
So for 10k tributepoints you could play with 26% haste for  ~140 hours. and since you can turn that on and off as you want it should last for a  very, very long time, since you most likely wont need haste always. Like when you chantkite = no use. if you hardly get to melee in your group = no use. If you use a instrument in primary = (almost) no use. aso.
<br />
If at lvl 40 you feel you need more Haste, you could get 31% haste for some more points per 10 minutes...and so on.
<br />

<br />
And if you are some day happy to get a good haste item (or a real augment from LdoN) - you can use your tributepoints for other stuff (FT, HP, Regen, ....)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
